Common Verbose Options & Usage:
Basic Verbose: nmap -v <target> (Shows progress, host discovery, and open ports as found).
Double Verbose: nmap -vv <target> (More detailed information, including DNS and scan completion times).
Verbose + OS Detection: nmap -v -O <target> (Provides details on OS fingerprinting).
Verbose + Version Detection: nmap -v -sV <target> (Shows version detection progress). 

Key Benefits of -v:
Real-time Feedback: Shows scan completion time estimates.
Faster Insight: Displays open ports as they are found, rather than waiting for the end of the scan.
Troubleshooting: Essential for diagnosing network issues or unexpected scan results.
Interactive Control: During a scan, you can press v or V to increase or decrease verbosity.

